Can't control my itchy hands and finally dived into setting up Jekyll (Github Pages) for this blog. It took me some time I admit - first time trying Ruby and all the commands via terminal. I'm aware of the easiest way that is via Jekyll-Now. But learning the manual way has its own advantages. 

By manual I mean setting up the environment and testing the server via command line. Hit a number of road blocks along the way but in hindsight isn't really complicated if you have the right environment and references to guide along.

I'm a Win user by MBP dual boot but setting up Jekyll is an exception. So on OSX here're some good references/pointers for first-timers:

1. Use this https://help.github.com/articles/using-jekyll-with-pages/ as your primary reference.

2. Use RVM (Ruby Version Manager) to make sure your version of Ruby is > 2.0.0.

3. Set up your yourusername.github.io page where you're pushing your pages - https://pages.github.com

